<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-476] Missing word/number in Operations Manual</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-476</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Current state reads:&lt;br/&gt;
Since Lustre 2.13, the &apos;overstriping&apos; feature is available, allowing more than stripe per OST.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Propose changing to &quot;more than one (1) stripe per OST.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FWIW, tried to make the change using Cygwin, however:&lt;br/&gt;
$ make check&lt;br/&gt;
xmllint --noout --xinclude --noent --relaxng ./index.xml&lt;br/&gt;
xmlRelaxNGParse: ./index.xml is empty&lt;br/&gt;
Relax-NG schema ./index.xml failed to compile&lt;br/&gt;
Usage : xmllint &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;options&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; XMLfiles ...&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
make: *** &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Makefile:45: check&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Error 5&lt;br/&gt;
$ ls -l index.xml&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;rw-rw-rw&lt;/del&gt; 1 brlee Domain Users 1692 Jul 22 09:01 index.xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If reasonably simple to resolve the problem and contribute, it would be nice to know how.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
